subject: Wrestling
lead_paragraph: . Henry Cejudo earned an Olympic berth for the United States in the 121-pound freestyle division in the Pan American Wrestling Championships in Colorado Springs. Cejudo pinned Andy Gonzales of Cuba in the second round of their title match. Cejudo is not yet assured a trip to Beijing. Olympic qualifying events give berths to countries, not individual wrestlers. Cejudo and others still must qualify at the United States trials on June 13-15 in Las Vegas.
